cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a self-supervised approach to deep surface deformation for shape matching, which involves using cycle-consistency to define a notion of good correspondences in groups of objects. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV) for its focus on shape matching and segmentation, graphics (cs.GR) for its use of surface deformation, machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) for its use of a neural network, and multimedia (cs.MM) for its use of shape representations.
